WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.272 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.272 --> 00:00:12.200 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:13.200 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:20.070 align:middle line:84%
>>1968 comes to a close,
such a time, a new age,

00:00:20.070 --> 00:00:22.690 align:middle line:90%
but the same sad story.

00:00:22.690 --> 00:00:25.770 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.770 --> 00:00:28.640 align:middle line:84%
In this time, Thomas
Merton is seen

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:31.320 align:middle line:84%
as a man whose
vision and writing

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:35.630 align:middle line:84%
brings hope to a
world in short supply.

00:00:35.630 --> 00:00:40.670 align:middle line:84%
But there are some who say
he is a heretic, while others

00:00:40.670 --> 00:00:47.461 align:middle line:84%
accuse him of using religion
to hide from the real world.

00:00:47.461 --> 00:00:48.751 align:middle line:90%
Who is he really?

00:00:48.751 --> 00:01:00.050 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.050 --> 00:01:02.109 align:middle line:90%
[HOOTING]

00:01:02.109 --> 00:01:08.030 align:middle line:90%


00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:10.080 align:middle line:84%
The year began
with Merton living

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:13.304 align:middle line:84%
as a hermit in the
Kentucky woods.

00:01:13.304 --> 00:01:19.130 align:middle line:84%
It will be the most momentous
year in his remarkable life.

00:01:19.130 --> 00:01:23.650 align:middle line:84%
And he begins it with a lively
celebration of the New Year.

00:01:23.650 --> 00:01:25.398 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:25.398 --> 00:01:29.310 align:middle line:90%


00:01:29.310 --> 00:01:35.130 align:middle line:10%
>>This will be a sort of
a New Year's Eve party,

00:01:35.130 --> 00:01:36.320 align:middle line:10%
I guess, from now on.

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:38.110 align:middle line:90%
It's getting-- I'm up late.

00:01:38.110 --> 00:01:39.120 align:middle line:90%
It's 7:00 o'clock.

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:41.003 align:middle line:84%
And instead of going
to bed, I'm going

00:01:41.003 --> 00:01:42.522 align:middle line:84%
to sit around and
play some records.

00:01:42.522 --> 00:01:45.680 align:middle line:90%


00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:49.520 align:middle line:84%
So you are invited
to participate

00:01:49.520 --> 00:01:54.130 align:middle line:84%
in this New Year's
Eve party of one,

00:01:54.130 --> 00:01:57.350 align:middle line:84%
or rather two, me and my
girlfriend, Mary Lou Williams.

00:01:57.350 --> 00:02:01.270 align:middle line:90%


00:02:01.270 --> 00:02:04.810 align:middle line:84%
But Mary Lou Williams
is on a record.

00:02:04.810 --> 00:02:07.480 align:middle line:90%
She is a Kansas City pianist.

00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:10.979 align:middle line:84%
I am an addict of
Kansas City jazz.

00:02:10.979 --> 00:02:15.150 align:middle line:10%
The closeness takes me back
to days 25, 30 years ago

00:02:15.150 --> 00:02:16.882 align:middle line:10%
in Greenwich
Village, when we used

00:02:16.882 --> 00:02:20.040 align:middle line:10%
to have a couple of
boogie-woogie pianists

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:21.937 align:middle line:10%
around the corner
from where I lived.

00:02:21.937 --> 00:02:23.895 align:middle line:84%
And I used to be down
there almost every night.

00:02:23.895 --> 00:02:26.058 align:middle line:90%
And I don't know why I like it.

00:02:26.058 --> 00:02:26.952 align:middle line:90%
But I like it.

00:02:26.952 --> 00:02:28.920 align:middle line:84%
It makes a great
deal of sense to me.

00:02:28.920 --> 00:02:34.480 align:middle line:90%


00:02:34.480 --> 00:02:40.670 align:middle line:84%
>>Thomas Merton is
born in France in 1915.

00:02:40.670 --> 00:02:44.540 align:middle line:90%
His parents are both artists.

00:02:44.540 --> 00:02:48.830 align:middle line:84%
He is an orphan
by the age of 16.

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:53.710 align:middle line:10%
Times of struggle
and search follow,

00:02:53.710 --> 00:03:02.770 align:middle line:10%
wine; women; a baby,
maybe; communism, briefly;

00:03:02.770 --> 00:03:07.432 align:middle line:10%
Catholicism, intensely; monk.

00:03:07.432 --> 00:03:13.950 align:middle line:84%
He enters the Abbey of
Gethsemani in December of 1941.

00:03:13.950 --> 00:03:16.420 align:middle line:90%
He is a man in love.

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:20.930 align:middle line:84%
He writes a best
seller about his love.

00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:26.100 align:middle line:84%
More books follow,
many more books.

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:30.276 align:middle line:90%
He is acclaimed internationally.

00:03:30.276 --> 00:03:34.140 align:middle line:84%
Then, after years of petitioning
his religious superiors,

00:03:34.140 --> 00:03:37.800 align:middle line:84%
he is allowed to
live as a hermit.

00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:41.200 align:middle line:90%
It's what he's always wanted.

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:46.339 align:middle line:84%
Still, he is a restless
man in a restless time.

00:03:46.339 --> 00:03:49.692 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.692 --> 00:03:52.566 align:middle line:90%
[BIRD CRIES]

00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:57.595 align:middle line:10%
>>The year struggles with its
own blackness, dark, wet mush

00:03:57.595 --> 00:04:02.270 align:middle line:10%
of snow under frozen
rain for two days.

00:04:02.270 --> 00:04:06.388 align:middle line:10%
A desolation of wetness
and waste, turning to mud.

00:04:06.388 --> 00:04:07.384 align:middle line:90%
[RUMBLING HELICOPTER]

00:04:07.384 --> 00:04:08.380 align:middle line:90%


00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:12.680 align:middle line:84%
Incredible barbarity
of the Vietnam War,

00:04:12.680 --> 00:04:16.829 align:middle line:84%
the weapons used, the ways of
killing utterly defenseless

00:04:16.829 --> 00:04:17.779 align:middle line:90%
people.

00:04:17.779 --> 00:04:20.180 align:middle line:90%
It is appalling.

00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:22.180 align:middle line:84%
Surely the moral
sense of this country

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:26.070 align:middle line:84%
is eroded, except that
there are protests.

00:04:26.070 --> 00:04:29.220 align:middle line:84%
How few know even a
little of the facts.

00:04:29.220 --> 00:04:31.580 align:middle line:90%
Certainly, this can't go on.

00:04:31.580 --> 00:04:33.143 align:middle line:90%
The country is under judgment.

00:04:33.143 --> 00:04:36.770 align:middle line:90%


00:04:36.770 --> 00:04:42.910 align:middle line:84%
>>Once, his words
were pious, edifying.

00:04:42.910 --> 00:04:45.850 align:middle line:90%
Now, they can sting.

00:04:45.850 --> 00:04:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Some wonder what's become
of the holy monk they

00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:52.000 align:middle line:90%
thought they knew?

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:58.330 align:middle line:84%
You made terribly wild, immoral
statements about our country.

00:04:58.330 --> 00:05:01.850 align:middle line:84%
>>You can't prove them
and you know you can't.

00:05:01.850 --> 00:05:05.470 align:middle line:84%
>>For a priest to
so engage himself

00:05:05.470 --> 00:05:10.780 align:middle line:84%
brands his activity as immoral,
reprehensible, disloyal,

00:05:10.780 --> 00:05:15.230 align:middle line:84%
and violating of his
sacred duty and trust.

00:05:15.230 --> 00:05:17.760 align:middle line:84%
>>Here is a human being
who is frightened to death

00:05:17.760 --> 00:05:21.860 align:middle line:84%
that nuclear energy is going to
cause the end of the world, who

00:05:21.860 --> 00:05:25.350 align:middle line:84%
therefore goes around screaming
at the top of his lungs,

00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:26.440 align:middle line:90%
stop the war!

00:05:26.440 --> 00:05:29.000 align:middle line:90%
For God's sake, stop the war.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.500 align:middle line:90%


00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:35.920 align:middle line:84%
>>Do you really want to
be a Christian or not?

00:05:35.920 --> 00:05:42.130 align:middle line:84%
Or do you want to be an
abstraction, a Zen mystic?

00:05:42.130 --> 00:05:44.290 align:middle line:84%
>>You don't have to
justify your life.

00:05:44.290 --> 00:05:47.160 align:middle line:90%


00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>>Tell me, how can you
justify the isolation

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.345 align:middle line:90%
of a hillside hermitage?

00:05:52.345 --> 00:05:57.560 align:middle line:90%


00:05:57.560 --> 00:06:01.190 align:middle line:84%
>>I get the strong
impression that you

00:06:01.190 --> 00:06:02.675 align:middle line:90%
are in some period of crisis.

00:06:02.675 --> 00:06:11.390 align:middle line:90%


00:06:11.390 --> 00:06:14.070 align:middle line:10%
>>I'm accused of living
in the woods like Thoreau,

00:06:14.070 --> 00:06:17.940 align:middle line:10%
instead of living in the desert
like Saint John the Baptist.

00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:21.230 align:middle line:10%
All I can answer is that I
am not living like anybody

00:06:21.230 --> 00:06:24.810 align:middle line:10%
or unlike anybody.

00:06:24.810 --> 00:06:26.880 align:middle line:10%
What I wear is pants.

00:06:26.880 --> 00:06:28.730 align:middle line:10%
What I do is live.

00:06:28.730 --> 00:06:32.240 align:middle line:90%
How I pray is breathe.

00:06:32.240 --> 00:06:36.780 align:middle line:84%
>>Oh, what is a monk to do
in these troubled times?

00:06:36.780 --> 00:06:39.990 align:middle line:84%
>>That depends on whom
you ask, of course.

00:06:39.990 --> 00:06:46.020 align:middle line:84%
Dom James Fox has definite
ideas of what a monk should do.

00:06:46.020 --> 00:06:51.750 align:middle line:84%
As the abbot of Merton's
monastery, he is in control.

00:06:51.750 --> 00:06:57.050 align:middle line:84%
Merton's hermitage is less
than a mile from the monastery.

00:06:57.050 --> 00:07:00.160 align:middle line:84%
But they are very
different places.

00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:01.952 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:07:01.952 --> 00:07:03.310 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:07.450 align:middle line:84%
>>In the monastery, we call
Thomas Merton Father Louis.

00:07:07.450 --> 00:07:09.550 align:middle line:84%
Actually, it's
Father Mary Louis.

00:07:09.550 --> 00:07:13.810 align:middle line:84%
In our life, you become a
new man and so a new name.

00:07:13.810 --> 00:07:18.680 align:middle line:84%
I've been Father Louis'
superior since 1948.

00:07:18.680 --> 00:07:20.230 align:middle line:90%
They have been good years.

00:07:20.230 --> 00:07:23.510 align:middle line:90%
And he's been a good monk.

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:26.050 align:middle line:84%
I have told more
than one person he

00:07:26.050 --> 00:07:30.760 align:middle line:84%
has been the most obedient
monk in the monastery.

00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:34.140 align:middle line:84%
Our relationship will
be changing soon.

00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:38.010 align:middle line:84%
But as I always say, all
for Jesus through Mary,

00:07:38.010 --> 00:07:41.010 align:middle line:90%
with a smile.

00:07:41.010 --> 00:07:46.340 align:middle line:84%
>>The abbot is a
very powerful man.

00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:52.960 align:middle line:84%
The Church a monk must rely on
his abbot to find God's will.

00:07:52.960 --> 00:07:58.510 align:middle line:10%
Merton and Dom James Fox
struggled with this situation.

00:07:58.510 --> 00:08:02.055 align:middle line:10%
It is a struggle
with a long history.

00:08:02.055 --> 00:08:05.769 align:middle line:90%


00:08:05.769 --> 00:08:08.204 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:08:08.204 --> 00:08:13.580 align:middle line:90%


00:08:13.580 --> 00:08:17.330 align:middle line:10%
>>Reverend Father, I
fully recognize your right

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:20.490 align:middle line:10%
to refuse permission
for a leave of absence.

00:08:20.490 --> 00:08:22.480 align:middle line:84%
In this, you were
following your conscience

00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:24.510 align:middle line:90%
and within your rights.

00:08:24.510 --> 00:08:27.700 align:middle line:84%
But I wonder about the way in
which you have done everything

00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:30.760 align:middle line:84%
possible to prevent me
from obtaining permission

00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:34.400 align:middle line:84%
from anyone and in
any way whatsoever.

00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:36.900 align:middle line:90%
I do not deny you this right.

00:08:36.900 --> 00:08:39.030 align:middle line:84%
But in point of
fact, it seems to me

00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:43.145 align:middle line:84%
to represent an arbitrary
and tyrannical spirit.

00:08:43.145 --> 00:08:46.830 align:middle line:90%


00:08:46.830 --> 00:08:48.420 align:middle line:84%
>>Good Father
Louis, as you know,

00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:50.670 align:middle line:84%
is really a genius
at writing books.

00:08:50.670 --> 00:08:54.250 align:middle line:84%
He's very dynamic and
bubbling over with energy.

00:08:54.250 --> 00:08:58.420 align:middle line:84%
And he has a very
expansive imagination.

00:08:58.420 --> 00:09:00.760 align:middle line:84%
To me, the whole
problem is that God

00:09:00.760 --> 00:09:03.720 align:middle line:84%
has one plan of life
for Father Louis.

00:09:03.720 --> 00:09:06.440 align:middle line:84%
And good Father Louis
is trying to follow

00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:10.760 align:middle line:84%
another one, different from
what God has planned for him.

00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:13.454 align:middle line:84%
The result is, of course,
terrific conflict.

00:09:13.454 --> 00:09:15.864 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:09:15.864 --> 00:09:17.310 align:middle line:90%


00:09:17.310 --> 00:09:21.590 align:middle line:10%
>>Do you not tend to assume
that your policies represent

00:09:21.590 --> 00:09:25.810 align:middle line:10%
the last word in the spiritual
perfection of every one

00:09:25.810 --> 00:09:30.470 align:middle line:10%
of your subjects and that anyone
who is drawn to another way

00:09:30.470 --> 00:09:32.650 align:middle line:10%
is leaving the
path of perfection,

00:09:32.650 --> 00:09:35.840 align:middle line:10%
simply because he is not
following your ideas?

00:09:35.840 --> 00:09:38.680 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:43.070 align:middle line:84%
>>As yet, of course, Father is
so obsessed with his own plan

00:09:43.070 --> 00:09:45.600 align:middle line:84%
that he cannot quite
see or, at least,

00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:50.530 align:middle line:84%
is not yet quite docile
enough to accept God's will.

00:09:50.530 --> 00:09:53.390 align:middle line:84%
But I think in the end
this spirit of faith

00:09:53.390 --> 00:09:56.650 align:middle line:84%
and increased spirit of
obedience and humility

00:09:56.650 --> 00:09:58.268 align:middle line:90%
will finally triumph.

00:09:58.268 --> 00:10:00.638 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:10:00.638 --> 00:10:05.380 align:middle line:90%


00:10:05.380 --> 00:10:07.820 align:middle line:84%
>>I have always
striven to be perfectly

00:10:07.820 --> 00:10:10.510 align:middle line:90%
obedient to legitimate commands.

00:10:10.510 --> 00:10:14.400 align:middle line:84%
But I beg the right to form
my conscience without demands

00:10:14.400 --> 00:10:18.460 align:middle line:84%
that I follow your
direction and no other.

00:10:18.460 --> 00:10:20.840 align:middle line:84%
I hope you understand
this rightly,

00:10:20.840 --> 00:10:23.240 align:middle line:90%
as a humble and filial petition.

00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:25.760 align:middle line:90%


00:10:25.760 --> 00:10:28.400 align:middle line:90%
>>My how they played each other.

00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And still the good
abbot trusted Merton

00:10:31.170 --> 00:10:35.952 align:middle line:84%
to instruct and help form the
novice monks of Gethsemani.

00:10:35.952 --> 00:10:39.120 align:middle line:84%
It is one of the most important
jobs in the monastery.

00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:42.350 align:middle line:90%


00:10:42.350 --> 00:10:44.830 align:middle line:84%
>>In our community, he is
the master of students.

00:10:44.830 --> 00:10:48.270 align:middle line:84%
He's very well liked by
every one of the students.

00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:51.450 align:middle line:84%
They look upon him as an
oracle of spirituality

00:10:51.450 --> 00:10:54.410 align:middle line:84%
and lean heavily upon
him for their guidance

00:10:54.410 --> 00:10:56.350 align:middle line:90%
in the spiritual life.

00:10:56.350 --> 00:10:58.590 align:middle line:84%
If he were ever
to leave here, it

00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:02.620 align:middle line:84%
would be a source of great
scandal to our young monks

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:04.730 align:middle line:84%
and would betray
them to the spirit

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:07.031 align:middle line:90%
of instability and change.

00:11:07.031 --> 00:11:09.386 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:11:09.386 --> 00:11:13.630 align:middle line:90%


00:11:13.630 --> 00:11:16.030 align:middle line:84%
>>Reverend Father,
I propose to you

00:11:16.030 --> 00:11:17.840 align:middle line:84%
that I should spend
a period of time

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:21.225 align:middle line:84%
in Japan, at one
of our monasteries,

00:11:21.225 --> 00:11:24.520 align:middle line:84%
in such a way as to be able
to visit some Zen monasteries

00:11:24.520 --> 00:11:27.090 align:middle line:84%
and meet those
interested in Zen.

00:11:27.090 --> 00:11:30.290 align:middle line:84%
This project would be most
important, not only for me

00:11:30.290 --> 00:11:33.320 align:middle line:84%
personally, but also
for the community here,

00:11:33.320 --> 00:11:35.220 align:middle line:90%
and indeed for the whole Church.

00:11:35.220 --> 00:11:38.020 align:middle line:90%
[BELLS TOLLING]

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:40.690 align:middle line:84%
>>Concerning his relations
with the outside world,

00:11:40.690 --> 00:11:44.250 align:middle line:84%
both Catholic and
non-Catholic, good Father Louis

00:11:44.250 --> 00:11:46.680 align:middle line:84%
does not realize that
he is a public figure

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:49.410 align:middle line:90%
of tremendous importance.

00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:53.090 align:middle line:84%
In my travels, I hear comments
on how much confidence priests

00:11:53.090 --> 00:11:56.350 align:middle line:84%
and religious place in
Father Louis and his writing.

00:11:56.350 --> 00:11:59.660 align:middle line:84%
Here again, there would be
tremendous scandal for them

00:11:59.660 --> 00:12:04.760 align:middle line:84%
to know that he is really quite
restless and unsure of himself.

00:12:04.760 --> 00:12:06.670 align:middle line:84%
His influence as
a writer would be

00:12:06.670 --> 00:12:08.570 align:middle line:90%
destroyed in a marked degree.

00:12:08.570 --> 00:12:13.220 align:middle line:90%


00:12:13.220 --> 00:12:15.630 align:middle line:84%
Father Louis wrote to
a respected theologian

00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:16.590 align:middle line:90%
for his opinion.

00:12:16.590 --> 00:12:19.730 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote back,
Father, I think

00:12:19.730 --> 00:12:22.420 align:middle line:84%
that God's will rivets
you to Gethsemani as he

00:12:22.420 --> 00:12:24.790 align:middle line:90%
was riveted to this cross.

00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:28.010 align:middle line:84%
Father, I do not think
that under any condition

00:12:28.010 --> 00:12:30.200 align:middle line:90%
you can leave Gethsemani.

00:12:30.200 --> 00:12:36.056 align:middle line:84%
You are wedded to it until
death, for better or for worse.

00:12:36.056 --> 00:12:37.478 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:12:37.478 --> 00:12:40.330 align:middle line:90%


00:12:40.330 --> 00:12:43.380 align:middle line:84%
>>I am both a prisoner
and an escaped prisoner.

00:12:43.380 --> 00:12:46.450 align:middle line:90%


00:12:46.450 --> 00:12:48.910 align:middle line:90%
>>Round and round, they go.

00:12:48.910 --> 00:12:53.270 align:middle line:84%
For 20 years, two gifted men
doing what they believe they

00:12:53.270 --> 00:12:55.440 align:middle line:90%
are called to do.

00:12:55.440 --> 00:13:02.790 align:middle line:84%
Then, in early 1968,
Dom James retirees

00:13:02.790 --> 00:13:06.455 align:middle line:90%
to a hermitage of his own.

00:13:06.455 --> 00:13:08.395 align:middle line:90%
[BIRD CRIES]

